 diagram, we\nexplicitly construct the invertible linear map $M : \\mathcal{P} \\longrightarrow\n\\mathcal{R}$, where $\\mathcal{R}$ (resp. $\\mathcal{P}$) is the root system\n(resp. partial root system) corresponding to $\\Gamma$ (resp.\n$\\widetilde\\Gamma$). In particular, we have $|\\mathscr{L}(\\widetilde\\Gamma)| =\n|\\mathscr{L}(\\Gamma)|$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Jun 2014 20:14:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 15 Jun 2014 08:38:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-06-17"}
